00:38:22,041 --> 00:38:23,462
If you can just add these features,

776
00:38:23,702 --> 00:38:24,883
make your community happy,

777
00:38:25,364 --> 00:38:26,805
so that it feels like a more complete game.

778
00:38:28,507 --> 00:38:30,008
Onboarding, we do it regularly,

779
00:38:30,109 --> 00:38:31,910
just like I explained with the chapter,

780
00:38:31,930 --> 00:38:35,173
to support a new player, to explain new mechanics.

781
00:38:35,733 --> 00:38:38,936
We actually released the game with two videos,

782
00:38:38,976 --> 00:38:40,237
that was our tutorial,

783
00:38:40,817 --> 00:38:43,519
and they became outdated really, really quickly.

784
00:38:44,580 --> 00:38:46,642
So we had to get rid of the videos,

785
00:38:46,682 --> 00:38:48,823
and we changed that to a manual,

786
00:38:49,084 --> 00:38:51,405
so text-based explanation and tutorial,

787
00:38:51,746 --> 00:38:53,407
and that was much easier to update.

788
00:38:53,887 --> 00:38:56,650
So it's a much better choice for a long-term onboarding.

789
00:38:59,042 --> 00:39:02,884
Quality of life are updates that lowers frictions

790
00:39:02,944 --> 00:39:03,604
within the game.

791
00:39:04,824 --> 00:39:08,126
One example that we lived recently,

792
00:39:08,306 --> 00:39:10,948
we had issues sometime with our matchmaking,

793
00:39:11,028 --> 00:39:14,669
sometime people would be with players that would be laggy,

794
00:39:15,570 --> 00:39:18,551
and they had no way to know their ping.

795
00:39:18,892 --> 00:39:19,372
So they would...

796
00:39:20,252 --> 00:39:24,417
go out of the game and use a third party software to be able to know the ping of the players.

797
00:39:24,577 --> 00:39:27,379
And we didn't want that, we didn't want players to get out of the game for that.

798
00:39:27,420 --> 00:39:32,785
So we've added this feature to the game, lowers friction, makes the experience better for all the players.

799
00:39:33,826 --> 00:39:36,849
And these guys are based on community needs.

800
00:39:37,009 --> 00:39:41,193
So when community is asking, requesting for something like that, we make it happen.

801
00:39:42,997 --> 00:39:45,597
Safety, not glamorous, but something that we have to do

802
00:39:46,017 --> 00:39:49,458
always, so every day, making sure that the game is a safe

803
00:39:50,118 --> 00:39:50,738
environment.

804
00:39:51,958 --> 00:39:55,299
We've added a lot of features, actually, since release.

805
00:39:56,139 --> 00:39:58,780
Report function, so a way to report players.

806
00:40:00,180 --> 00:40:04,341
Ban function, and also making sure that the new cheats and

807
00:40:04,361 --> 00:40:07,841
the new cheat engine are addressed, so that there's no

808
00:40:07,881 --> 00:40:08,502
cheating in the game.

809
00:40:10,925 --> 00:40:13,887
Events is one of the most interesting ones, something

810
00:40:13,907 --> 00:40:15,829
that we started last year, actually.

811
00:40:16,569 --> 00:40:21,854
So Halloween, a winter event, the anniversary, they're great

812
00:40:22,294 --> 00:40:25,477
to create excitement around the event for a week or a

813
00:40:25,537 --> 00:40:29,000
weekend, and they're a great way to test

814
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:30,221
special gameplay as well.

815
00:40:32,393 --> 00:40:35,455
and they are great to lower the toxicity for a moment.

816
00:40:35,676 --> 00:40:37,377
Every time we do events with Objective

817
00:40:37,417 --> 00:40:38,918
that are usually community-based,

818
00:40:39,879 --> 00:40:42,481
we see that within the game, the toxicity is lowered,

819
00:40:42,761 --> 00:40:44,603
it brings the community members together,

820
00:40:44,963 --> 00:40:45,904
so that's really interesting.

821
00:40:47,365 --> 00:40:49,307
And last one but not least, balance,

822
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:50,868
something we do regularly as well,

823
00:40:51,188 --> 00:40:53,790
so to balance issues and to shape meta.

824
00:40:54,030 --> 00:40:57,453
So I'll go back with more on balance a little bit later.

825
00:40:59,235 --> 00:41:00,616
So lesson here is really to

826
00:41:01,882 --> 00:41:04,064
if you're aiming to have a live game

827
00:41:04,104 --> 00:41:05,565
that you're gonna update regularly,

828
00:41:06,305 --> 00:41:07,946
you need to focus on the foundation

829
00:41:08,226 --> 00:41:09,387
of your game at the beginning.

830
00:41:09,527 --> 00:41:12,669
It's okay to cut a lot of secondary system

831
00:41:13,669 --> 00:41:15,350
because you'll have time afterwards.

832
00:41:15,631 --> 00:41:18,292
If the players buy in and wanna be part

833
00:41:18,312 --> 00:41:19,353
of the experience of your game,

834
00:41:19,813 --> 00:41:21,354
then the rest can come later

